=== 11.8 Python Implementation

`cross-entropy-loss` computes stem:[-\log P(\text{true token})] for a single position.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=loss]
----

`sequence-loss` averages the per-position losses into one scalar — the training signal for a complete sequence.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=loss]
----

The softmax-cross-entropy gradient has a famously clean closed form:
stem:[\partial \mathcal{L} / \partial z_j = P(j) - \mathbf{1}[j = \text{true}\]].

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=loss]
----

Run with `python3 src/python/chapter_demos.py`.
Expected output:

----
Per-position losses:
  pos 0 (true=3): loss=1.609  P(true)=0.200
  pos 1 (true=4): loss=0.511  P(true)=0.600
  pos 2 (true=0): loss=0.916  P(true)=0.400
  pos 3 (true=2): loss=0.223  P(true)=0.800

Mean loss: 0.815
Perplexity: 2.26
----
